{"title": "Curse Is Foiled Again", "content": "A Curse that has run for so long that the cursed has forgotten what pre-cursed life was like is finally broken. A tidal wave of good fortune follows immediately after, implying that all the good luck had been bottled up by the presence of the curse and is now pouring out by the gallons to compensate for the hardships endured by the cursed for years (and sometimes generations).\n\nThis is most likely to occur when the curse was clearly undeserved by its sufferers; in cases when the curse is deserved, the karmic aftermath is usually reduced to a simple return to pre-cursed status quo with an Aesop learned.\n\nActually breaking the curse seems to be limited to film and one-shots: TV shows are extremely fond of making every attempt to break the curse a failure to preserve the status quo, especially if the character is Cursed with Awesome.\n\nThe title is a pun on a stock line uttered by the Dastardly Whiplash.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurseIsFoiledAgain", "media_links": ["https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/XXXenophile", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Holes", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DisneyAnimatedCanon", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/BeautyAndTheBeast", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JustMyLuck", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ChrisPine", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DeltoraQuest", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JackVance", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DyingEarth", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheLegendOfRahAndTheMuggles", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBible", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LittleDorrit", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/PoulAnderson", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki